---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Contact | civilrightscalc.com';
const description = 'Contact the civilrightscalc.com editorial team with corrections, feedback, or questions about civil rights law and § 1983 content.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Contact</h1>
  <p>For corrections, feedback, or questions about our content, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>. We read every message.</p>

  <h2>What we can help with</h2>
  <p>We welcome messages about factual inaccuracies, outdated legal citations, errors in calculator formulas, or suggestions for topics we should cover. If you find a case citation that has been reversed or a legal standard that has changed since our last update, please let us know — we take accuracy seriously and will review and update content promptly when errors are confirmed.</p>

  <h2>What we cannot help with</h2>
  <p>We cannot provide legal advice or respond to requests for case-specific analysis. Evaluating whether you have a viable &sect; 1983 claim, whether qualified immunity applies to your situation, or what damages you might recover requires an attorney familiar with your specific facts and the applicable case law in your circuit. For that, consult a civil rights attorney — most take &sect; 1983 cases on contingency and offer free initial consultations.</p>
  <p>We also cannot respond to press inquiries, partnership requests, or solicitations for paid content placements. All editorial content is produced independently without commercial arrangements.</p>
</BaseLayout>
